slmm                  package:spmodel                  R Documentation

_F_i_t _a _s_p_a_t_i_a_l _l_i_n_e_a_r _m_i_x_e_d _m_o_d_e_l

_D_e_s_c_r_i_p_t_i_o_n:

     Fit a spatial linear mixed model

_U_s_a_g_e:

     slmm(
       formula,
       data,
       xcoord,
       ycoord = NULL,
       cov_type,
       cov_initial,
       estmethod = "reml",
       weights = "cressie",
       ...
     )
     
_A_r_g_u_m_e_n_t_s:

 formula: A formula specifying the fixed effect structure

    data: A data frame, sf object, or sp object

  xcoord: x-coordinate column name in ‘data’ (not required if data is
          an sf or sp object)

  ycoord: y-coordinate column name in ‘data’ (if spatial domain is two
          dimensional (not required if data is an sf or sp object)

cov_type: The covariance type: ‘"exponential"’, ‘"spherical"’,
          ‘"gaussian"’, or ‘"matern"’. Not required if ‘cov_initial’ is
          provided. In this event, ‘cov_type’ assumes all covariance
          parameters are unknown and will be estimated.

cov_initial: A ‘cov_initial’ object specifying the initial values for
          optimization and any known parameters. Not required if
          ‘cov_type’ is provided.

estmethod: The estimation method: ‘"reml"’ or ‘"ml"’ for restricted
          maximum likelihood and maximum likelihood, respectively
          (Patterson and Thompson, 1971; Harville, 1977; Wolfinger and
          Sall, 1993); ‘"sv-wls"’ for semivariogram weighted least
          squares estimation (Cressie, 1985); ‘"cl"’ for composite
          likelihood (Curriero and Lele, 1999)#'

 weights: Weights to use if ‘estmethod = "svwls"’: Possible values are
          ‘"cressie"’, ‘"ols"’, ‘"pairs"’, or ‘"pairs-invd"’

     ...: Additional arguments to ‘esv()’ or ‘optim()’

_V_a_l_u_e:

     A list with many model components

_E_x_a_m_p_l_e_s:

     slmm(y ~ x, exdata, xcoord, ycoord, "exponential")
     

